The pilot stated that after landing the tail started to go right of centerline. He applied right 
rudder with little to no effect. He then applied brakes, but applied them too hard and the tail 
came off the ground and the airplane nosed over inverted. The pilot reported no mechanical 
problems with the airplane.
The pilot's improper use of brakes during landing roll resulting in a nose-over.
History of Flight
Landing-landing roll
Nose over/nose down (Defining event)
